-- Rosneft sees 2013 capex at $20 billion post TNK-BP deal
-- 
-- Tue Apr 23, 2013 7:22am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/04/23/us-rosneft-capex-idUSBRE93M0F420130423

 

 MOSCOW  (Reuters) - Rosneft ( ROSN.MM ) expects capital expenditure of $20 billion this year following the acquisition of TNK-BP TNBP.MM, Rosneft's Chief Executive Officer Igor Sechin said on Tuesday. 
 The previous guidance for Rosneft's capex this year was $15 billion, while TNK-BP expected it at to be around $6 billion. Sechin told investors during a presentation that the company is able to reduce spending following the deal to acquire TNK-BP. (Reporting by Vladimir Soldatkin; editing by  Megan Davies )